tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,"O thou folded in garments!"
  73,5,"Soon shall We send down to thee a weighty Message."
  73,8,"But keep in remembrance the name of thy Lord and devote thyself to Him whole-heartedly."
  73,9,"(He is) Lord of the East and the West: there is no god but He: take Him therefore for (thy) Disposer of Affairs."
  73,14,"One Day the earth and the mountains will be in violent commotion. And the mountains will be as a heap of sand poured out and flowing down."
  73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed the messenger; so We seized him with a heavy Punishment."
  73,18,"Whereon the sky will be cleft asunder? His Promise needs must be accomplished."